# Version & Model Tracking

## Always Display Version

In every response where you make code changes, deploy, or push, display the current version:

> `vYYMMDD.NN H:MMa/p [model]`

Read from `version.json` (field: `version` + `model`) or from `bump-version.sh` output.

## Model Self-Reporting

When running `bump-version.sh`, you MUST pass `--model` with your model code:

```bash
./scripts/bump-version.sh --model o4.6
```

Model code format is a short `x0.0` identifier:
- `o4.6` = Claude Opus 4.6
- `s4.0` = Claude Sonnet 4
- `g2.5` = Gemini 2.5
- `g4o` = GPT-4o
- `cur` = Cursor (unknown model)

Never omit `--model`. If unsure of your exact model, use the closest identifier.

## Deploy Workflow

```bash
./scripts/bump-version.sh --model MODEL   # Bump version with model tag
git add -A
git commit -m "Description"
git push
```

Post-push, always report: **Deployed to main** -- version `vYYMMDD.NN H:MMa/p` `[model]`
